          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "## Context\n\nThe pd-ocr-labeler / pd-ocr-labeler-spa labeler UI carries an `is_validated: bool` flag per WordMatch — a reviewer marks a word as \"I have verified this OCR/GT match is correct.\" Today that flag lives only in the labeler-side `WordMatch` model (legacy `pd_ocr_labeler/models/word_match_model.py:34` and SPA `pd_ocr_labeler_spa/core/models.py:174`).\n\nSpec `pd-ocr-labeler-spa/specs/23-page-payload-backend.md §9` calls for a `Word.set_validated(bool)` method on the OCR-level Word — so the validated state can round-trip through `to_dict()` / `from_dict()` and the labeler doesn't have to maintain a parallel SPA-only set keyed on `(line_index, word_index)`.\n\n## Ask\n\nAdd to `pd_book_tools/ocr/word.py`:\n\n- A persisted boolean field (e.g. `is_validated: bool = False`) on `Word`.\n- A `set_validated(self, value: bool) -> bool` setter that returns True iff the value changed (parity with `apply_component` etc.).\n- Round-trip in `to_dict()` / `from_dict()` so the envelope persists the flag.\n\nThis is a non-breaking additive change (default False = current behavior).\n\n## Why\n\n- pd-ocr-labeler-spa is implementing word-mutation endpoints (issue #315) and must store per-word validated state somewhere. Without a `Word.is_validated`, the SPA either bolts on a parallel `dict[tuple[int,int], bool]` (extra state to serialize / drift risk) or hacks the flag onto the `Word` instance via `setattr` (lost on `from_dict` round-trip).\n- Legacy labeler already exposes the concept; the spec wants pd-book-tools to be the persistent home.\n\n## Workaround until then\n\npd-ocr-labeler-spa stores the flag on a `PageState.validated_words: dict[tuple[int,int], bool]` map; the route handler updates that map and the cached envelope omits the flag. Flag is **lost on envelope reload** until this issue lands.\n\n## Refs\n\n- pd-ocr-labeler-spa `specs/23-page-payload-backend.md §9` (the line `\\| .../words/{l}/{w}/validated \\| word.set_validated(bool) \\|`)\n- pd-ocr-labeler-spa issue ConcaveTrillion/pd-ocr-labeler-spa#315 (spec-23-C1 word mutations)",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-19T10:26:29Z",
          "comments": {
            "nodes": [
              {
                "author": {
                  "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
                },
                "body": "Won't do — word.review.validated is the correct access pattern. A top-level accessor leaks ReviewMetadata's fields into Word and breaks the encapsulation the sub-object provides.",
                "createdAt": "2026-05-19T10:26:28Z",
                "id": "IC_kwDOONYVBs8AAAABC29XHA",
